hopobject.body: I'm a partner in bupropion sr 100mg tablets (12 h) During a 2009 promotional tour for his film 'Two Lovers,' also starring Gwyneth Paltrow, Phoenix appeared on David Letterman's couch sporting a shaggy beard, sunglasses, and a whacked-out attitude, proclaiming he was giving up acting to pursue a hip-hop career. Skeptics protested that the star was trying to pull off an elaborate hoax and even Paltrow called her co-star's behavior 'odd,' but Phoenix's rep repeatedly defended the career switch. Though he never admitted the bizarre behavior was fake, in January of 2010 a clean-cut Phoenix spoofed his spacey appearance on Letterman in a video for a charity campaign.
